            "description": "We designed a simulation board game and used it to create social learning about how to make tradeoffs among these competing values, and to be played among different cities landscapes in terms of tourism issues and policy making styles demonstrate the value of a simulation approach to support future planning processes.\n\nThe developed board game can represent multiple cities around the world and the issues they are facing in terms of tourism. The game is assisted with a digital dashboard which, supports the physical elements in the board game based on a model developed by experts.\n\nI was the technical manager and the lead producer on this project, which is touring European cities, with great outcomes.",
