                }
            },
            "description": "The MSP Challenge uses game technology and role-play to support communication and learning for Marine/Maritime Spatial Planning. In short, is a data driven multi-player game, that can load multiple world regions with real geodata, and allow through advanced realistic simulations, the players to understand the impact of specific policies and plans done for a sea basin. At the moment we support 3 different regions: North Sea, Baltic Sea, and Clyde River (Scothland)\n\nI part in this project, was the technical manager of the project, were I designed the systems architecture, the protocols and different simulations and coordinated the development team for the MSP Challenge Simulation Platform. ",
